lead_paragraph: Michael Phelps lowered his world record in the 200-meter butterfly last night at the Pan Pacific Championships in Victoria, British Columbia, coming from behind on the final lap to win in 1 minute 53.80 seconds. Jess Schipper of Australia set the women’s world record in the event in 2:05.40.
